This paper discusses the challenges and solutions for network-wide resource allocation in wireless network virtualization (WNV), which is a topic related to computer networks (cs.NI) and system and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) for resource allocation, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits and customization of WNV, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
